Deep whales: preprocessing and stats¶

Summary¶

In this notebook we aim to:

  • Assess image color schema [DONE: all converted into grayscale]
  • Apply mask to dim background [DONE: Sobel mask was selected, following Michele]
  • Augment unfrequent categories with random shear, rotation, vertical reflection and zoom [HALF DONE: in approach 1 we augment all categories except for 'new_whale' to match a target frequency (50, 100?), in approach 2 we apply a linear augmentation as n_new_samples = 40/33*n_old_samples + 290/33]
  • Crop augmented images into squares and save to background [UNDONE: we need something smarter than this]

Note: given the high frequency of 'new_whale' and given that new_whales may have nothing in common with each other it would appear advantageous to exclude new_whale from training, to compute 5 most probable whales and to add artificially new_whale into the set based on a theoretical probability threshold.

# check what fraction of images are grayscale (copied from another Notebook)
def is_gray_scale(img_path):
    # https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23660929/how-to-check-whether-a-jpeg-image-is-color-or-gray-scale-using-only-python-stdli
    im = Image.open(img_path).convert('RGB')
    w,h = im.size
    for i in range(w):
        for j in range(h):
            r,g,b = im.getpixel((i,j))
            if r != g != b: return False
    return True

In [37]:
pixel_width = 225

def preprocess_whale(img_path, save=True, w=pixel_width):
    
    img = io.imread(img_path, as_gray=True)
    maximum = np.amax(img)
    if maximum <= 1.0: 
        img = img*255
    img = sobel(img)
    img = resize(img, (w, w),mode = 'reflect', anti_aliasing=True)
    maximum = np.amax(img)
    if maximum <= 1.0: 
        img = img*255
    img = img.astype("uint8")

    if save == True:  
        name = img_path.split(".")[-2].split("/")[-1]
        imageio.imwrite(path_preprocessed + name + ".jpg", img)
        #scipy.misc.imsave(path_gray_sodel + name + ".png",  img, format=None)
    
    return None

In [45]:
def get_whale_tensor(whale_id):
    all_pics = id_dict[whale_id]
    all_pics = [io.imread("data/train_preprocessed/" + k, as_gray=True) for k in all_pics]
    all_pics = [k.reshape((1,) + (1,) + k.shape) for k in all_pics]
    tensor = all_pics[0]
    for item in all_pics[1:]:
        tensor = np.concatenate((tensor,item),axis=0)
    return tensor

In [47]:
def augment_tensor(name, tensor, max_images=100):
    i=0
    for batch in datagen.flow(tensor, batch_size=tensor.shape[0], shuffle=True, save_format='jpg'):
        for j in range(batch.shape[0]):
            if i >= max_images:
                return None
            img = batch[j,0,:,:]
            img = img.astype("uint8")
            imageio.imwrite(path_prepocessed_augmented + name + "-" + str(i+1) +  ".jpg", img)
            i+=1
In [48]:
def augment_whale(whale_id, max_images=100):
    start_tensor = get_whale_tensor(whale_id)
    images_at_start = start_tensor.shape[0]
    if whale_id == 'new_whale':
        return None
    augment_tensor(whale_id, start_tensor, max_images=max_images)

# define function to get image size
def get_size(paths_list):
    sizes = []
    for item in paths_list:
        img_shape = mpimg.imread(item).shape
        sizes.append(img_shape)
    return sizes
